<page api="portableSql">
    <shortlink>portablesql concatenate function</shortlink>
    <topic  parent="" parentType="" elementName="Concatenate Portable SQL Function">Concatenate</topic>
    <description>
        <p>Concatenate a list of strings and return the result.</p>
    </description>
    <prototypes>
        <prototype>Concatenate as C (Arg1 as C [, Arg2 as C ...])</prototype>
    </prototypes>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>Arg1</name>
            <type>C</type>
            <description>
                <p>A field or value.</p>
            </description>
        </argument>
        <argument optional="true">
            <name>Arg2...ArgN</name>
            <type>C</type>
            <description>
                <p>Additional fields or values.</p>
            </description>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <returns>
        <return>
            <name>result</name>
            <type>C</type>
            <description>
                <p>Returns the concatenated string.</p>
            </description>
        </return>
    </returns>
    <discussion>
        <p>The Concatenate function creates a string by concatenating one or more values together. For example:</p>
    </discussion>
    <example code="sql"  caption="Concatenate() function executed on the Northwind Access database"><![CDATA[SELECT FIRST 1 Concatenate(City,', ',Country) AS Expr1 FROM Customers
=Berlin, Germany]]></example>
</page>